.TH DISCORD_GATEWAY_CONNECT 3 "2026-06-29" "libdiscord 0.2.0" "libdiscord Programmer's Manual"
.SH NAME
discord_gateway_connect \\\\- establish Gateway WebSocket connection via librest binary channel
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
#include <discord.h>

int discord_gateway_connect(discord_ctx_t *ctx);
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B discord_gateway_connect
initiates a Gateway WebSocket connection by calling librest's
.B rest_establish_binary_channel
to perform an HTTP/2 extended CONNECT handshake. On success, the context transitions to
DISCORD_GW_CONNECTING state (and subsequently to DISCORD_GW_CONNECTED when the binary channel is ready, as reported by the
.B REST_EVENT_BINARY_CHANNEL_READY
event from librest).

This is a pure plumbing call — it generates the HTTP/2 extended CONNECT frames but performs no I/O. The caller must send the output bytes over the network (via
.BR discord_get_output (3))
and feed responses back (via
.BR discord_feed_input (3)).

After connection is established, the caller should:
.IP 1. 3
Wait for
.B DISCORD_EVENT_CONNECTED
event
.IP 2. 3
Wait for Gateway Hello (op 10) — heartbeat interval is captured automatically
.IP 3. 3
Send identify via
.BR discord_gateway_send_identify (3)
.IP 4. 3
Begin heartbeat loop via
.BR discord_gateway_process_heartbeat (3)
.SH RETURN VALUES
0 on success (frames generated), -1 on error (NULL ctx, missing librest context, or channel establishment failure). On failure, the gateway state resets to DISCORD_GW_DISCONNECTED.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
discord_config_t cfg = {
    .event_queue_size = 64,
    .bot_token = "MTIzNDU2..."
};
discord_ctx_t *bot = discord_create_with_config(DISCORD_ROLE_CLIENT, &cfg);

int rc = discord_gateway_connect(bot);
if (rc == 0) {
    /* Extract output frames for network I/O */
    uint8_t buf[8192];
    int n = discord_get_output(bot, buf, sizeof(buf));
    send_to_gateway(buf, n);
}
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
discord_create(3), discord_gateway_send_identify(3), discord_gateway_send_heartbeat(3), discord_gateway_state(3), discord_feed_input(3), discord_get_output(3)
.SH NOTES
The context must have a valid bot token configured before calling this function. The binary channel establishment uses HTTP/2 extended CONNECT (RFC 8441) to negotiate a WebSocket connection to the Discord Gateway URL.
